    "80, [0.22, 1.87] d = 0.95, [0.90, 1.00] d = 1.27 [1.11, 1.42] Effect of framing on decision-making (Tversky & Kahneman, 1981) In a scenario of buying both a cheap item and an expensive item, subjects answered whether they would buy at a far-away store with a fixed discount on either the cheap item or the expensive item OR = 4.96 [2.55, 9.90] OR = 2.06 [1.87, 2.27] \"correct answer\" effect Table 1 (continued) Study Description Original ML2 GPT Reluctance to tempt fate (Risen & Gilovich, 2008) In the role of a student in class, subjects estimated their likelihood of being called on when being told they had not prepared for class (tempting fate) versus being told they had prepared (not tempting fate)",
